# Risk Action Tracker — With Escalation Logic

*This is a thinking exercise, not a real organisation.*

---

## Purpose

This tracker exists to ensure that identified risks are converted into completed actions.

It links directly to:
- AI Risk Register  
- Risk Acceptance decisions  
- Board and Risk Committee reporting  

> A risk that has been identified but not actioned is not managed — it is documented.

This tracker makes open risk actions visible, owned, and time-bound.

---

## Scope

This tracker captures:

- All remediation actions arising from risk register entries  
- Actions linked to risk acceptance conditions  
- Actions arising from incidents, audits, or regulatory reviews  

---

## Action Status Definitions

| Status | Definition |
|------|-----------|
| Open | Action agreed but not yet started |
| In Progress | Action actively being worked |
| At Risk | Likely to miss deadline |
| Overdue | Deadline passed without completion |
| Completed | Action delivered and validated |
| Closed | Completed and no longer requires tracking |

---

## Escalation Rules

| Condition | Escalation |
|----------|-----------|
| Action at risk (within 7 days of deadline) | Notify risk owner |
| Action overdue (0–14 days) | Escalate to Head of GRC |
| Action overdue (>14 days) | Escalate to Executive (CRO / COO) |
| Action overdue (>30 days) | Report to Risk Committee / Board |

> Escalation is automatic. It is not dependent on the action owner choosing to report.

